WEBVTT

00:02:29.983 --> 00:02:31.133
and you get to wonder.

00:02:31.157 --> 00:02:33.185
Now, I love science, don't get me wrong.

00:02:33.209 --> 00:02:35.332
My parents emigrated
from a war-torn country,

00:02:35.356 --> 00:02:36.578
came to America,

00:02:36.602 --> 00:02:41.427
and science for them was, like,
more their identity than anything else,

00:02:41.451 --> 00:02:43.518
and I inherited that from them.

00:02:44.268 --> 00:02:46.737
But there was something
about that simple movement

00:02:46.761 --> 00:02:48.047
from science to wonder

00:02:48.071 --> 00:02:49.908
that just started to feel wrong to me.

00:02:49.933 --> 00:02:52.051
Like, is that the only path
a story can take?

00:02:52.945 --> 00:02:54.599
Around 2012,

00:02:54.823 --> 00:02:59.076
I ran into a bunch of different stories
that made me think, "No."

00:02:59.466 --> 00:03:00.632
One story in particular,